Apple juice-agar plates
0.6 g methyl 4-hydroxybenzoate
10.0 g sucrose
250 mL apple juice
9.0 g Bacto agar
300 mL H2O

Prepare the apple juice solution by adding the first two ingredients to the apple juice. Boil and then let cool.

Prepare the agar solution by adding the Bacto agar to the H2O. Boil.

Mix the apple juice and agar solutions, cool to 65ÂºC, and pour into Petri dishes. 
